remarks.format:
## Remarks

`ColorExtensions` provides extension methods for converting between
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorF>, and <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor>.

Note that <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor> uses ARGB byte ordering (`0xAARRGGBB`), while
<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor> uses BGRA byte ordering (`0xBBGGRRAA`). These extension
methods handle the conversion transparently.

## Examples

```csharp
// Convert SKColor to HBColor
SKColor skColor = SKColors.CornflowerBlue;
HBColor hbColor = skColor.ToHBColor();

// Convert HBColor back to SKColor
SKColor back = hbColor.ToSKColor();
```
